TopicTitle: Just got KSP and its stuck on loading screen "Loading Part Upgrades"

Articles.Content: I downloaded KSP a few hours ago and have spent atleast 1 hour on the loading screen. I deleted save states, reinstalled a couple times, tried to run on Rosetta,  changed to beta version, nothing works. It's stuck on "Loading Parts Upgrading"

Sounds like the game is encountering a problem during the loading process which usually stops the game loading but doesn’t cause it to crash or exit. The best way to find the cause and fix it is to post your log files so someone can take a look, here’s how:

What are you trying to run KSP on i.e. PC, laptop, chrome book etc. and what are the hardware specs? KSP is limited mostly by RAM during loading and by CPU in flight so those matter most, but you may also have issues if your hard drive has insufficient free space.

Edited April 18, 2023 by jimmymcgoochie
